%% Data Flow Diagram for vllm-gaudi
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as RHOAI Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant KServe as KServe Ingress<br/>80/TCP HTTP
    participant vLLM as vLLM API Server<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    participant HPU as Intel Gaudi HPU<br/>SynapseAI Runtime
    participant S3 as Object Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant HF as HuggingFace Hub<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over Client,HPU: Flow 1: Model Inference Request

    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    Gateway->>KServe: Forward (HTTP/80)<br/>TLS terminated
    KServe->>vLLM: Forward (HTTP/8000)<br/>Internal routing
    vLLM->>HPU: Execute model forward pass<br/>HPU runtime (PCIe)
    HPU-->>vLLM: Inference result
    vLLM-->>KServe: JSON Response
    KServe-->>Gateway: Response
    Gateway-->>Client: HTTPS Response<br/>TLS 1.2+

    Note over Client,HPU: Flow 2: Multi-HPU Distributed Inference

    participant Ray as Ray Head<br/>6379/TCP
    participant Worker as HPUWorker (rank N)<br/>HCCL/RDMA

    Ray->>Worker: Distribute execution<br/>Ray protocol (dynamic port)
    vLLM->>HPU: Forward pass (rank 0)
    HPU->>Worker: HCCL all-reduce/all-gather<br/>RDMA (dynamic port)
    Worker-->>HPU: Synchronized tensors
    HPU-->>vLLM: Combined result

    Note over Client,HPU: Flow 3: Disaggregated Prefill/Decode (NIXL)

    participant Prefill as Prefill Instance
    participant NIXL as NIXL Agent<br/>RDMA/TCP
    participant Decode as Decode Instance

    Prefill->>NIXL: KV-cache transfer<br/>RDMA/TCP (dynamic)
    NIXL->>Decode: KV-cache delivery<br/>RDMA/TCP (dynamic)

    Note over vLLM,S3: Model Loading (startup)

    vLLM->>S3: Download model weights<br/>HTTPS/443 AWS IAM
    S3-->>vLLM: Model artifacts
    vLLM->>HF: Download tokenizer/config<br/>HTTPS/443 Bearer Token
    HF-->>vLLM: Model files
